reviews.review: This movie could not possibly save the franchise from the Last Jedi
I think this movie was great for the awful plot line set up from TLJ, I expected much worse so I'm satisfied.
The second you don't create a road-map for your series, then you know you done fucked it up.

Spoiler warning

1.Bad comedy (jokes take the audience right out of the moment)
2. Bad soundtrack
3. Filled with plot holes and inconsistencies 
4. Premise of the movie that darth sidious returns not only feels unplanned but ruins every film before it
5. Many rules grounded in the star wars universe are broken without explanation (primarily using the force the bring back the dead)
6 movie feels rushed
7. Movie makes it so obvious that there was no endgoal planned for this trilogy
8. Even the action is boring and lightsbaer duels and space battles r dull
9. Steals too many elements from original star wars trilogy similar to in tfa
10. Too much ex machina moments
11. Characters always make stupid descisions
12.  Many times character r persumed dead or have some sort of conflict but they immediatyl come back or the conflict is resolved immediately thus ruining any tension.
13. Characters use new overpowered force abilities that no one used before without any explanation of how they learned these abilities and y they havent been used before by other force users.
14. Most characters have no character development and moments in movie feel unearned
14. Did i mention plot holes cuz there r too many (theres a youtube vid by shadiversity that names a few)

Good story line
Too much light saber fighting
Better than Return of the Jedi
it had its stupid moments that didn't make sense but it was so entertaining and well made that you just were kind of able to ignore those parts

The exciting movie of the new trilogy!  The beginning was a bit too fast paced, trying to get in as many retcons from The Last Jedi as possible.  Definitely enjoyed it, and thought it was a nice sendoff to the Skywalker saga with throwbacks all throughout.
When C3P0 is the best part of your movie, you know you're doing a lot of things wrong.

The problem with this movie is that instead of telling a story and not caring about what anybody thinks, too many scenes were shot with the feeling that "a focus group would like or didn't like this" the movie felt forced and felt very commercialized,  instead of presenting a story that made any sense or gave justice to the established story arcs, the movie feels as if EVERY scene was made with the audience in mind. To make a truly great movie you've got to have a solid story that doesnt worry about what someone is gonna like or dislike,  this definitely wasnt the case. overall the movie was entertaining but it does a discredit to the star wars saga and pays too much fan service trying to appease the masses...you can certainly tell it was a modern Disney production
